OL,4,Cson in court ordered to pay
OL,5,Ccompensation
OL,7,FShe added that if he was an adult, he
OL,8,Fwould be going to jail for up to five
OL,9,Fyears, but she was giving him a
OL,10,F"chance" and instead ordered him to
OL,11,Fcomplete a 12-month referral order.
OL,13,FThe boy, who has ADHD, was described
OL,14,Fas a "lovely affection little boy," by
OL,15,Fhis mother, but who had at times a
OL,16,F"chaotic" home life.
OL,18,FHe told the judge he was "sorry", now
OL,19,Fhad help from social workers and had
OL,20,Ftaken up boxing.
